  "text": "Protocol 1: 30% Percoll gradient centrifugation as described [CITATION_1] . Samples were divided into 13 1-ml fractions. Radioactivity peaked in fraction 3, which contained 25% of ␤-hexosaminidase activity, 15% of ␣-mannosidase II activity, 76% of NADPH-cytochrome c reductase activity, 26% of 5Јnucleotidase activity, and 64% of radioactivity. Protocol 2: The sucrose concentration of postnuclear supernatants was adjusted to 60% (wt/vol). The solution was overlaid with a linear 50 -15% sucrose gradient and centrifuged at 40,000 rpm for 16 h in a SW40T rotor. Protocol 3: 2 10-cm dishes of J774 cells were labeled with [ 3 H]cholesteryl ether, and a postnuclear supernatant was prepared as described above. Sucrose was added to a final concentration of 50%. The mixture was overlaid with a 50 -10% linear sucrose gradient in buffer B and centrifuged at 40,000 rpm for 210 min in an SW40T rotor.",
